   "source": [
    "# GDP per Capita Analysis with Pandas\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook performs a simple exploratory data analysis (EDA) on a GDP per capita dataset using Pandas and Matplotlib.\n",
    "\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4bd18803",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports and data loading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a775f0d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the dataset (adjust the path or filename if needed)\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/gdp_per_capita.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9943c9c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Basic inspection\n",
    "\n",
    "Check the structure, data types, and basic statistics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6864cc11",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a25f9315",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.describe(include='all')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3c5bd2d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Select relevant columns\n",
    "\n",
    "For this analysis we focus on:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `Country/Territory`\n",
    "- `UN_Region`\n",
    "- `GDP_per_capita`\n",
    "\n",
    "Update the column names below if your dataset uses slightly different labels."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3763cb9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Rename columns if necessary (uncomment and edit to match your file)\n",
    "# df = df.rename(columns={\n",
    "#     'Country or Area': 'Country/Territory',\n",
    "#     'Region': 'UN_Region',\n",
    "#     'GDP (nominal) per capita': 'GDP_per_capita'\n",
    "# })\n",
    "\n",
    "cols_to_keep = ['Country/Territory', 'UN_Region', 'GDP_per_capita']\n",
    "df = df[cols_to_keep]\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "926589cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Handle missing values\n",
    "\n",
    "Check for missing data and decide how to handle it (drop or fill)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1c9bf524",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df.isna().sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4d21d529",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# For simplicity, drop rows with any missing values in key columns\n",
    "df_clean = df.dropna(subset=['Country/Territory', 'UN_Region', 'GDP_per_capita'])\n",
    "\n",
    "df_clean.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a3c5adb0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. GDP per capita by UN region\n",
    "\n",
    "Compute the average GDP per capita for each region and sort regions from richest to poorest."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "45a1d5b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "region_gdp = (\n",
    "    df_clean\n",
    "    .groupby('UN_Region')['GDP_per_capita']\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "region_gdp"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c0af1912",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5.1 Visualise average GDP per capita by region"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "94405703",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "region_gdp.plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Average GDP per capita')\n",
    "plt.title('Average GDP per capita by UN Region')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "947a8199",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Top and bottom countries by GDP per capita"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b52a55ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Top 10 countries\n",
    "top_10 = df_clean.sort_values(by='GDP_per_capita', ascending=False).head(10)\n",
    "top_10"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d402927a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Bottom 10 countries\n",
    "bottom_10 = df_clean.sort_values(by='GDP_per_capita', ascending=True).head(10)\n",
    "bottom_10"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2246aae3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.1 Visualise top 10 countries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "41214035",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.barh(top_10['Country/Territory'], top_10['GDP_per_capita'])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('GDP per capita')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 10 Countries by GDP per Capita')\n",
    "plt.gca().invert_yaxis()  # highest at the top\n",
    "plt.grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fb3daa7b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Distribution of GDP per capita\n",
    "\n",
    "Plot a histogram to see how GDP per capita is distributed across all countries."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "acc3dd2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "df_clean['GDP_per_capita'].plot(kind='hist', bins=30)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('GDP per capita')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of GDP per Capita')\n",
    "plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5bd025f9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Conclusions\n",
    "\n",
    "From this simple analysis we can:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Compare the average GDP per capita across UN regions\n",
    "- Identify the top and bottom countries by GDP per capita\n",
    "- Observe the overall distribution of GDP per capita values\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Loading and cleaning a CSV dataset with Pandas\n",
    "- Selecting and renaming columns\n",
    "- Handling missing values\n",
    "- Grouping and aggregating by region\n",
    "- Ranking and visualising countries by GDP per capita\n",
    "- Plotting distributions with Matplotlib"
   ]
  }
 ],
